  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this research study is to look at a new rehabilitation technique for
      individuals who have suffered a stroke and have difficulties walking. This study is designed
      to compare robot-assisted (Lokomat) rehabilitation therapy with standard physical therapy in
      order to improve walking post-stroke. This research project will be conducted as a pilot
      randomized controlled trial that compares the effectiveness of Lokomat versus conventional
      physical therapy in improving the ambulation and gait of chronic stroke patients. The project
      will provide important pilot data that could indicate whether or not the effectiveness of
      Lokomat training is superior to that of standard physical therapy and if a definitive and
      larger clinical trial is warranted.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
